mice called the Agouti mice.

00:24:40.160 --> 00:24:42.780 align:middle line:84%
Now, the Agouti mice,
the poor little things,

00:24:42.780 --> 00:24:47.610 align:middle line:84%
were basically bred to
be floppy, fat, yellow,

00:24:47.610 --> 00:24:50.750 align:middle line:84%
because the yellow color was
tied in with the activation

00:24:50.750 --> 00:24:51.980 align:middle line:90%
of their fat gene.

00:24:51.980 --> 00:24:52.850 align:middle line:90%
All right?

00:24:52.850 --> 00:24:56.800 align:middle line:84%
And then, what they did was they
decided to take the females,

00:24:56.800 --> 00:24:59.340 align:middle line:84%
and they decided to
just do one thing,

00:24:59.340 --> 00:25:00.660 align:middle line:90%
feed them something different.

00:25:00.660 --> 00:25:03.740 align:middle line:84%
Instead of the junk they usually
ate, feed them something that

00:25:03.740 --> 00:25:07.050 align:middle line:84%
gave them methyl
donors to shut down,

00:25:07.050 --> 00:25:11.140 align:middle line:84%
clamp down the gene that
was making them fat.

00:25:11.140 --> 00:25:13.080 align:middle line:84%
So they went ahead
and fed these mothers,

00:25:13.080 --> 00:25:16.720 align:middle line:84%
you know, leafy greens,
folate, a lot of B vitamins.

00:25:16.720 --> 00:25:19.290 align:middle line:84%
And lo and behold,
they had pups.

00:25:19.290 --> 00:25:20.920 align:middle line:84%
And everyone waited.
You know?

00:25:20.920 --> 00:25:22.920 align:middle line:84%
And they found out
that the pups, instead

00:25:22.920 --> 00:25:26.720 align:middle line:84%
of being floppy and yellow
and also destined to die young

00:25:26.720 --> 00:25:30.390 align:middle line:84%
from all kinds of diseases,
ended up being lean and brown,

00:25:30.390 --> 00:25:35.000 align:middle line:84%
meaning that simply
using leafy greens

00:25:35.000 --> 00:25:39.880 align:middle line:84%
shut down the Agouti gene,
which is the obesity gene.

00:25:39.880 --> 00:25:42.020 align:middle line:84%
And they were able
to breed completely

00:25:42.020 --> 00:25:46.380 align:middle line:84%
normal mice with no disease
that could live a long life.

00:25:46.380 --> 00:25:50.290 align:middle line:84%
Thus was the birth
of epigenetics,

00:25:50.290 --> 00:25:53.690 align:middle line:84%
which means that you have
control over gene expression,

00:25:53.690 --> 00:25:55.860 align:middle line:84%
no matter what your mother
and father gave you.

00:25:55.860 --> 00:25:58.797 align:middle line:84%
So this was done in one
generation with the mice?

00:25:58.797 --> 00:26:00.230 align:middle line:84%
DR. PEEKE: This was
done in one generation.

00:26:00.230 --> 00:26:03.260 align:middle line:84%
And it affected multiple
generations, proving

00:26:03.260 --> 00:26:05.430 align:middle line:90%
that DNA is not destiny.

