00:35:20.160 --> 00:35:24.770 align:middle line:84%
For some people, it's
salty, starchy foods.

00:35:24.770 --> 00:35:26.460 align:middle line:84%
For other people,
it's, you know, tons

00:35:26.460 --> 00:35:28.126 align:middle line:84%
of bread with tons of butter.
LISA: Uh-huh.

00:35:28.126 --> 00:35:29.350 align:middle line:84%
For other people,
it's all sweets.

00:35:29.350 --> 00:35:30.882 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't matter what it is.

00:35:30.882 --> 00:35:32.910 align:middle line:84%
You know what your crack
is because you feel

00:35:32.910 --> 00:35:34.720 align:middle line:90%
out of control when you eat it.

00:35:34.720 --> 00:35:35.640 align:middle line:90%
All right?

00:35:35.640 --> 00:35:37.680 align:middle line:84%
So you take that,
and you eliminate it.

00:35:37.680 --> 00:35:40.820 align:middle line:84%
And what you then do
is you give yourself

00:35:40.820 --> 00:35:44.670 align:middle line:84%
incredibly wonderful,
healthy fixes in its place.

00:35:44.670 --> 00:35:49.120 align:middle line:84%
And what I did was I actually
teamed with a phenomenal group

00:35:49.120 --> 00:35:52.910 align:middle line:84%
of culinary nutritionists
who were able to sit down

00:35:52.910 --> 00:35:57.180 align:middle line:84%
and do battle with all of
the false fixes with the most

00:35:57.180 --> 00:36:00.020 align:middle line:84%
tasty, wonderful
recipes and food

00:36:00.020 --> 00:36:03.130 align:middle line:84%
plans so that you can get
through a gentle detox

00:36:03.130 --> 00:36:06.960 align:middle line:84%
over about four to six weeks
and then move onto Begin

00:36:06.960 --> 00:36:08.240 align:middle line:90%
a Recovery.

00:36:08.240 --> 00:36:10.870 align:middle line:84%
And in Begin a
Recovery, what you're

00:36:10.870 --> 00:36:13.000 align:middle line:84%
doing there is practicing,
practicing, practicing,

00:36:13.000 --> 00:36:14.280 align:middle line:90%
practicing, every day.

00:36:14.280 --> 00:36:15.210 align:middle line:90%
Mind, mouth, muscle.

00:36:15.210 --> 00:36:16.270 align:middle line:90%
Keep refining.

00:36:16.270 --> 00:36:17.591 align:middle line:84%
You will slip.
You will fall.

00:36:17.591 --> 00:36:18.290 align:middle line:90%
You will stand up.

00:36:18.290 --> 00:36:20.000 align:middle line:84%
You will dust off
your little behind.

00:36:20.000 --> 00:36:23.600 align:middle line:84%
You will keep going, and you
will achieve what you need to

00:36:23.600 --> 00:36:26.810 align:middle line:84%
in order to be able to move
into the final phase which

00:36:26.810 --> 00:36:28.400 align:middle line:90%
is Master Recovery.

00:36:28.400 --> 00:36:31.640 align:middle line:84%
And even if you're in Master
Recovery, it's circuitous.

00:36:31.640 --> 00:36:35.100 align:middle line:84%
You could come back if
you need to to detox

00:36:35.100 --> 00:36:36.700 align:middle line:90%
if something happens to you.

00:36:36.700 --> 00:36:39.370 align:middle line:84%
One of my patients ended
up with breast cancer.

00:36:39.370 --> 00:36:42.000 align:middle line:84%
And she had to, you
know, go through surgery,

00:36:42.000 --> 00:36:42.790 align:middle line:90%
all the rest of it.

00:36:42.790 --> 00:36:44.530 align:middle line:90%
Eating was a little funky.

00:36:44.530 --> 00:36:47.590 align:middle line:84%
She came back through it,
right back up to Master.

00:36:47.590 --> 00:36:48.310 align:middle line:90%
Mm.

00:36:48.310 --> 00:36:50.515 align:middle line:84%
You are so incredibly
motivating.

00:36:50.515 --> 00:36:51.931 align:middle line:84%
Can I just have you
in my living room?

00:36:51.931 --> 00:36:53.480 align:middle line:84%
I mean it.
[LAUGHTER]

00:36:53.480 --> 00:36:56.800 align:middle line:84%
No, the book is amazing because
it makes so much clear sense.

00:36:56.800 --> 00:36:58.690 align:middle line:84%
You use so much
science to validate

00:36:58.690 --> 00:36:59.590 align:middle line:90%
what you're talking about.

00:36:59.590 --> 00:37:01.970 align:middle line:84%
And then, it gives
recipes, which is the best.

00:37:01.970 --> 00:37:04.410 align:middle line:84%
But I have to ask you,
do you eliminate it

00:37:04.410 --> 00:37:05.700 align:middle line:90%
completely forever?

00:37:05.700 --> 00:37:09.020 align:middle line:84%
Can I never have my,
you know, my Americana

00:37:09.020 --> 00:37:10.410 align:middle line:90%
with vanilla again?

00:37:10.410 --> 00:37:12.580 align:middle line:84%
DR. PEEKE: Well, here's
what's interesting.

00:37:12.580 --> 00:37:14.471 align:middle line:84%
First, you have to
identify your crack.

00:37:14.471 --> 00:37:16.530 align:middle line:84%
OK?
Whatever it may be.

00:37:16.530 --> 00:37:19.910 align:middle line:84%
And some people, all they
have to do is see a drugstore.

00:37:19.910 --> 00:37:20.840 align:middle line:90%
It's a cue.

00:37:20.840 --> 00:37:23.290 align:middle line:84%
And inside are the
big bags of candy

00:37:23.290 --> 00:37:24.630 align:middle line:84%
that they used to
buy at the drugstore.

00:37:24.630 --> 00:37:26.680 align:middle line:84%
One of my patients, you
know, had this issue.

00:37:26.680 --> 00:37:27.740 align:middle line:90%
All right?

00:37:27.740 --> 00:37:35.110 align:middle line:84%
So for her, just being near
these big bags of candy

00:37:35.110 --> 00:37:37.860 align:middle line:84%
was a huge problem for
her for a very long time.

00:37:37.860 --> 00:37:40.070 align:middle line:84%
But you have to ask
yourself why would you want

00:37:40.070 --> 00:37:43.670 align:middle line:90%
to be exposed to crappy candy?

00:37:43.670 --> 00:37:46.250 align:middle line:84%
Why do you want
that again anyway?

00:37:46.250 --> 00:37:49.710 align:middle line:84%
So it's very different
than if you were asking me,

00:37:49.710 --> 00:37:53.420 align:middle line:84%
well, you know, I have some
issues with oatmeal raisin

00:37:53.420 --> 00:37:56.240 align:middle line:84%
cookies, and the next thing you
know, I'm eating 12 of them.

00:37:56.240 --> 00:37:59.350 align:middle line:84%
Can I ever have an oatmeal
raisin cookie again?

00:37:59.350 --> 00:38:01.710 align:middle line:84%
The question is
answered this way.

00:38:01.710 --> 00:38:05.380 align:middle line:84%
One, if you have
crossaddictions-- if you're

00:38:05.380 --> 00:38:08.740 align:middle line:84%
a smoker or have been,
alcoholic or you've had issues,

00:38:08.740 --> 00:38:11.820 align:middle line:84%
or it's strongly in your
family, drugs, whatever else,

00:38:11.820 --> 00:38:13.320 align:middle line:90%
the answer is probably no.

00:38:13.320 --> 00:38:15.810 align:middle line:84%
You probably should
not be re-exposed again

00:38:15.810 --> 00:38:20.950 align:middle line:84%
because you just have too strong
a vulnerability in that area.

00:38:20.950 --> 00:38:25.300 align:middle line:84%
If, however, none of that's
true, if you have a mild food

00:38:25.300 --> 00:38:27.950 align:middle line:84%
addiction that it's
under control now,

00:38:27.950 --> 00:38:30.640 align:middle line:84%
you've shed whatever weight
you need to, you already have

00:38:30.640 --> 00:38:33.110 align:middle line:84%
adopted all these other
habits, then ask yourself,

00:38:33.110 --> 00:38:37.540 align:middle line:84%
do I really need that food stuff
again and to revisit all this?

00:38:37.540 --> 00:38:39.190 align:middle line:90%
Most people would say no.

00:38:39.190 --> 00:38:41.200 align:middle line:84%
What about the emotional part
of it, where you're looking

00:38:41.200 --> 00:38:43.020 align:middle line:84%
for that food or
that fix because you

00:38:43.020 --> 00:38:45.740 align:middle line:84%
want to drown out some certain
emotion that's happening?

00:38:45.740 --> 00:38:48.790 align:middle line:84%
Well, then take 10
steps back, Lisa.

00:38:48.790 --> 00:38:50.660 align:middle line:84%
Stress management.
All right?

00:38:50.660 --> 00:38:54.620 align:middle line:84%
Why are you knee jerking
right back into a false fix?

00:38:54.620 --> 00:38:57.660 align:middle line:84%
There are many other things you
can do, lots of other things

00:38:57.660 --> 00:38:59.780 align:middle line:84%
you can do that are
healthier fixes.

00:38:59.780 --> 00:39:01.260 align:middle line:84%
LISA: And that goes
back to the drug

00:39:01.260 --> 00:39:02.980 align:middle line:84%
reward circuit in the brain.
-Absolutely.

00:39:02.980 --> 00:39:03.930 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:39:03.930 --> 00:39:04.980 align:middle line:90%
LISA: Which we have a slide of.

00:39:04.980 --> 00:39:06.320 align:middle line:84%
This is what it
looks like, right?

00:39:06.320 --> 00:39:08.760 align:middle line:84%
DR. PEEKE: And so once
again, what you're looking at

00:39:08.760 --> 00:39:12.540 align:middle line:84%
is you're looking at all of
the flooding of the dopamine

00:39:12.540 --> 00:39:16.860 align:middle line:84%
in people who have both, you
see a control, and the cocaine.

00:39:16.860 --> 00:39:19.390 align:middle line:84%
Tons and tons and
tons of that dopamine

00:39:19.390 --> 00:39:22.720 align:middle line:84%
just secreted all the way
through these receptors.

00:39:22.720 --> 00:39:26.310 align:middle line:84%
Eventually what happens is these
receptors are gonna decrease

00:39:26.310 --> 00:39:30.130 align:middle line:84%
in number because the
body cannot handle

00:39:30.130 --> 00:39:34.760 align:middle line:84%
the overwhelming amount of
dopamine that's showering

00:39:34.760 --> 00:39:36.780 align:middle line:90%
upon it in the brain.

00:39:36.780 --> 00:39:40.005 align:middle line:84%
And so when the brain gets
overflooded with the dopamine

00:39:40.005 --> 00:39:43.810 align:middle line:84%
and it gets into that place,
how do you get out of it?

00:39:43.810 --> 00:39:45.390 align:middle line:84%
I mean, when you're
in that state

00:39:45.390 --> 00:39:48.760 align:middle line:84%
of a complete out of control
binge, what do you do?

00:39:48.760 --> 00:39:50.680 align:middle line:90%
That's a very tough thing.

00:39:50.680 --> 00:39:53.870 align:middle line:84%
The first thing that is
really the main prerogative

00:39:53.870 --> 00:39:55.870 align:middle line:84%
is to prevent this
in the first place.

00:39:55.870 --> 00:39:58.000 align:middle line:84%
Because when you're
really on a bender,

00:39:58.000 --> 00:40:00.540 align:middle line:84%
that's a very
difficult thing to do.

00:40:00.540 --> 00:40:03.360 align:middle line:84%
You know, that's like telling--
that's like grabbing a bottle

00:40:03.360 --> 00:40:06.850 align:middle line:84%
out of the hand of an alcoholic
when they're really-- you know,

00:40:06.850 --> 00:40:08.940 align:middle line:84%
they've already had
their first two glasses.

00:40:08.940 --> 00:40:10.440 align:middle line:90%
That's very tough.

00:40:10.440 --> 00:40:12.160 align:middle line:84%
And I'll tell you
another reason why.

00:40:12.160 --> 00:40:17.800 align:middle line:84%
When you continuously re-expose
the body, the brain to whatever

00:40:17.800 --> 00:40:21.575 align:middle line:84%
substance it may be,
it craves more and more

00:40:21.575 --> 00:40:23.840 align:middle line:90%
at higher and higher levels.

00:40:23.840 --> 00:40:26.640 align:middle line:84%
So now, to stop it
is very difficult.

00:40:26.640 --> 00:40:29.180 align:middle line:10%
The whole issue with
"The Hunger Fix"

00:40:29.180 --> 00:40:31.620 align:middle line:10%
is to prevent this
in the first place,

00:40:31.620 --> 00:40:33.660 align:middle line:10%
to get you through that
detox and recovery,

00:40:33.660 --> 00:40:37.000 align:middle line:10%
and keep you vigilant for
the rest of your life.

00:40:37.000 --> 00:40:38.290 align:middle line:10%
Because you're right, Lisa.

00:40:38.290 --> 00:40:40.450 align:middle line:10%
You brought it up perfectly.

00:40:40.450 --> 00:40:42.050 align:middle line:10%
Look at us in America.

00:40:42.050 --> 00:40:43.515 align:middle line:90%
There's cues everywhere.

00:40:43.515 --> 00:40:44.280 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:40:44.280 --> 00:40:45.980 align:middle line:90%
Radio, print media.

00:40:45.980 --> 00:40:47.140 align:middle line:90%
LISA: Thousands of times a day.

00:40:47.140 --> 00:40:48.360 align:middle line:84%
Online.
LISA: Yes.

00:40:48.360 --> 00:40:49.060 align:middle line:90%
Everywhere.

00:40:49.060 --> 00:40:50.050 align:middle line:90%
What people say.

00:40:50.050 --> 00:40:52.430 align:middle line:84%
What people-- you
know, they may walk by.

00:40:52.430 --> 00:40:53.670 align:middle line:90%
You're sitting on an airplane.

00:40:53.670 --> 00:40:55.490 align:middle line:84%
They just brought a
whole bag of stuff

00:40:55.490 --> 00:40:57.720 align:middle line:84%
to eat on the airplane with
you, right next to you.

00:40:57.720 --> 00:40:58.800 align:middle line:90%
So you can't control the cues.

00:40:58.800 --> 00:40:59.330 align:middle line:84%
DR. PEEKE: You
can't control them.

00:40:59.330 --> 00:41:00.760 align:middle line:84%
They're going to
always be there.

00:41:00.760 --> 00:41:04.130 align:middle line:84%
DR. PEEKE: But you can control
your response to the cues.

00:41:04.130 --> 00:41:08.760 align:middle line:84%
And this is why having a very
buffed up prefrontal cortex

00:41:08.760 --> 00:41:09.470 align:middle line:90%
is where it's at.

00:41:09.470 --> 00:41:12.671 align:middle line:84%
That's why my motto in the book
is "big brain, small waist."

00:41:12.671 --> 00:41:14.410 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHTER]
-I love that.

00:41:14.410 --> 00:41:16.140 align:middle line:84%
One of the other things
I loved about the book

00:41:16.140 --> 00:41:19.080 align:middle line:84%
is the fact that it's
not one solution.

00:41:19.080 --> 00:41:20.521 align:middle line:84%
It's a minute to
minute solution.

00:41:20.521 --> 00:41:21.880 align:middle line:84%
DR. PEEKE: Right.
-Can you explain that?

00:41:21.880 --> 00:41:24.360 align:middle line:84%
DR. PEEKE: Every 24
hours-- you know,

00:41:24.360 --> 00:41:28.170 align:middle line:84%
it's what you see in all
addiction treatment, per se.

00:41:28.170 --> 00:41:30.710 align:middle line:84%
And that is you
live for 24 hours.

00:41:30.710 --> 00:41:33.610 align:middle line:84%
You don't stress about what's
happening five years from now.

00:41:33.610 --> 00:41:35.120 align:middle line:90%
You live for 24 hours.

00:41:35.120 --> 00:41:39.720 align:middle line:84%
So you say to yourself, how can
I stop cavin' to the cravin'?

00:41:39.720 --> 00:41:41.110 align:middle line:90%
How do I stop that?

00:41:41.110 --> 00:41:42.610 align:middle line:84%
So you look at
every single hour.

00:41:42.610 --> 00:41:43.530 align:middle line:90%
How have I prepared?

00:41:43.530 --> 00:41:45.200 align:middle line:90%
Do I have my appropriate foods?

00:41:45.200 --> 00:41:49.790 align:middle line:84%
And my avoiding, as best I can,
the people, places, and things

00:41:49.790 --> 00:41:51.910 align:middle line:90%
that cue me and trigger me.

00:41:51.910 --> 00:41:55.540 align:middle line:84%
And you may have to change
up how and where you live

00:41:55.540 --> 00:41:57.847 align:middle line:84%
and work to make this happen.
LISA: Interesting.

00:41:57.847 --> 00:41:58.580 align:middle line:90%
You know what I mean?

00:41:58.580 --> 00:42:01.030 align:middle line:84%
I you're trying to get off
alcohol, working at a bar

00:42:01.030 --> 00:42:03.090 align:middle line:84%
is probably not the
place to be, right?

00:42:03.090 --> 00:42:04.270 align:middle line:84%
I was going to
ask you how do you

00:42:04.270 --> 00:42:08.070 align:middle line:84%
coach your patients into
getting off of this addiction,

00:42:08.070 --> 00:42:10.430 align:middle line:90%
this false fix?

00:42:10.430 --> 00:42:11.970 align:middle line:90%
I get them into detox.

00:42:11.970 --> 00:42:14.390 align:middle line:84%
You know, what I do is I
detox them immediately.

00:42:14.390 --> 00:42:17.540 align:middle line:84%
I have them just sit down, be
honest, tell their true truth.

00:42:17.540 --> 00:42:18.740 align:middle line:90%
What is your crack?

00:42:18.740 --> 00:42:19.990 align:middle line:90%
What is your food crack?

00:42:19.990 --> 00:42:21.940 align:middle line:90%
Whatever it may be, you go home.

00:42:21.940 --> 00:42:23.440 align:middle line:90%
You get it out of the house.

00:42:23.440 --> 00:42:25.410 align:middle line:84%
I mean, people actually
keep this around.

00:42:25.410 --> 00:42:27.640 align:middle line:84%
Oh, well, I'll just keep
the ice cream around,

00:42:27.640 --> 00:42:29.490 align:middle line:84%
just-- wink, wink-- in case.
Right?

00:42:29.490 --> 00:42:30.260 align:middle line:90%
Really?

00:42:30.260 --> 00:42:31.970 align:middle line:90%
No, get it out of the house.

00:42:31.970 --> 00:42:35.471 align:middle line:84%
If it's something that's a
binge-able, cravable false fix,

00:42:35.471 --> 00:42:37.491 align:middle line:84%
get it out.
It's not working for you.

00:42:37.491 --> 00:42:38.190 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:42:38.190 --> 00:42:40.370 align:middle line:84%
I have to do this
with my own husband.

00:42:40.370 --> 00:42:42.000 align:middle line:84%
I have no problems
with ice cream.

00:42:42.000 --> 00:42:42.960 align:middle line:90%
He does.

00:42:42.960 --> 00:42:45.940 align:middle line:84%
In all the years
we've been together,

00:42:45.940 --> 00:42:48.140 align:middle line:84%
I've never been able to
keep ice cream in the house

00:42:48.140 --> 00:42:49.960 align:middle line:90%
because it's unsafe around him.

00:42:49.960 --> 00:42:52.860 align:middle line:84%
Now, he's athletic, in great
shape, and all the rest of it.

00:42:52.860 --> 00:42:56.720 align:middle line:84%
But you know, if that stuff's
around, he'll start obsessing.

00:42:56.720 --> 00:42:57.990 align:middle line:90%
It's a cue.

00:42:57.990 --> 00:43:00.260 align:middle line:84%
And so everyone
has a strange one.

00:43:00.260 --> 00:43:01.890 align:middle line:90%
And you'd never expect it.

00:43:01.890 --> 00:43:05.150 align:middle line:84%
Men and women equally
have this problem.

00:43:05.150 --> 00:43:06.850 align:middle line:84%
Oh, absolutely.
Absolutely.

00:43:06.850 --> 00:43:10.160 align:middle line:84%
I have this desire
for crunchy, salty.

00:43:10.160 --> 00:43:11.510 align:middle line:90%
That is my cue.

00:43:11.510 --> 00:43:12.410 align:middle line:90%
It's crunchy, salty.

00:43:12.410 --> 00:43:14.751 align:middle line:84%
And the minute it's in the
house, my husband eats it.

00:43:14.751 --> 00:43:15.910 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHTER]
DR. PEEKE: There it goes.

00:43:15.910 --> 00:43:16.734 align:middle line:90%
There it goes.

00:43:16.734 --> 00:43:18.000 align:middle line:84%
Well, we all have
something different.

00:43:18.000 --> 00:43:20.020 align:middle line:84%
And he says don't
bring it in the house.

00:43:20.020 --> 00:43:20.800 align:middle line:90%
DR. PEEKE: Mm-hm.

00:43:20.800 --> 00:43:22.090 align:middle line:90%
And he's right.

00:43:22.090 --> 00:43:23.270 align:middle line:90%
DR. PEEKE: Absolutely.

00:43:23.270 --> 00:43:25.720 align:middle line:84%
So in terms of not putting
the foods in your house--

00:43:25.720 --> 00:43:28.310 align:middle line:84%
and of course, you can
control your own environment.

00:43:28.310 --> 00:43:31.360 align:middle line:84%
But the outside environments,
what happens when

00:43:31.360 --> 00:43:32.990 align:middle line:90%
there is an emotion attached?

00:43:32.990 --> 00:43:36.480 align:middle line:84%
So have a friend who sets up
their vacations on the fact

00:43:36.480 --> 00:43:38.650 align:middle line:84%
that you can go different
places in these areas

00:43:38.650 --> 00:43:42.240 align:middle line:84%
to go eat because in the
past, her family went there.

00:43:42.240 --> 00:43:46.770 align:middle line:84%
And it's a good feeling that
she associated with food.

00:43:46.770 --> 00:43:48.060 align:middle line:84%
DR. PEEKE: Well,
you know, again,

00:43:48.060 --> 00:43:51.470 align:middle line:84%
in each one of those places,
